Title : Douglas Dias Jayasinha
Text : '''Douglas Dias Jayasinha''' (11 May 1915 – 28 April 2006) was a [[Ceylonese]] cricketer and cricket administrator.<ref name=ddj>[http://archives.dailynews.lk/2005/06/06/spo03.htm D. D. Jayasinha – brilliant cricketer cum administrator and the GOM SL Cricket]</ref> Born in [[Galle]], he was educated at [[Mahinda College]], where he captained his college cricket team from 1934 to 1936.<ref name=ddj/> A left-hand batsman, a handy bowler and slip fielder, he was one of the first from the south of the island to represent All-Ceylon, against New Zealand in 1937 and India in 1945.<ref name= wis>[http://www.espncricinfo.com/wisdenalmanack/content/story/245250.html Wisden Obituaries]</ref> He was a national selector from 1961 to 1973, the last ten years as chairman. He died on 28 April 2006, aged 90.<ref name= wis/>

